result.execSummary:
The defendant Fredina P. Harris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Deliver Illegal Articles to Inmate [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with S. Jackson and/or any State of Wisconsin Department of Corrections Institution - no correctional or penal institution maintained by the State, County and/or any other entity.   Defendant is not to be on the premises of any facility or prohibited from having any communication with any inmate of such a facility.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

timeConds.notes: Time served sentence with credit for 64 days.
